-- Bankia share trading suspension lifted on Monday
-- 
-- Mon May 28, 2012 3:00am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/28/us-bankia-trading-idUSBRE84R04Q20120528

 

 MADRID  (Reuters) - Spain's stock exchange regulator the CNMV said on Monday that trading in Bankia ( BKIA.MC ) shares would start again at 0830 CET, after it was suspended on Friday before the troubled bank announced a 19 billion euro ($23.77 billion) state rescue plan. 
 Bankia shares last closed on Friday at 1.57 euros. The stock has dropped over 56 percent since the start of the year. ($1 = 0.7992 euros) (Reporting by Sarah White, Editing by Jose Elias Rodriguez)